<br>
The reasons have been said many times, but Ill reiterate just to make sure we have some definite points to work on.<br>
<br>
Damage Chant: Should be increased a bit to bring it equal with most others (maybe an increase to 8, or 9 at max). The dropping every so often is annoying, but the only thing to fix that is possibly increase the effect time from 5 to 8, and have it 'recast' every 6 seconds. I do welcome the increased range.<br>
<br>
Snare shout: Relatively useless. In RVR combat, this has very little use. In PVE almost less, unless you are the puller for the group. If this was a Speed Debuff that increased with Battlesong skill, then it would be very much useful, and more group supportive.<br>
<br>
Mez shout: In the slew of RVR revamps (such as the Mez immunity), this shout was reduced in effectiveness. A stun would be more effective overall, with a max of maybe 6 seconds, kept on a 20 second timer.<br>
<br>
Skalds as a whole need something else to make them the group support class they are described. I know the suggestions of adding a new song to the line didnt seem to go over well, but maybe if we keep asking and looking for compromise, we may get somewhere.<br>
<br>
The possible best choices would be: Ablative Armor chant, Damage shield chant, a "proc" chant (similar to Reavers/Vales proc spells, but maybe a little less damage), or just an Armor Buff chant (like Paladins). Any of these would be good cases for allowing a second skald within the group.<br>
<br>
Just my two bits on this whole thing. Keep up the good work Rosie, I know the Skald community supports you every step of the way. <p>Bays Endruhms<br>
Skald of Drott Grimmastr<br>
