<br>
To be honest, I didn't notice the extra HP - I still got down to 1/4 health fighting yellows while wearing orange equipment (no, its not SC'd, I don't have as much money as you lvl 50s.. I'm only 44)<br>
<br>
Anyway - I agree that we need more to offer a group. In a group with 2 skalds, if we're in a dungeon, one of us is running health chant and the other is running damage. What most people don't realize is that health chant is an increase in regen rate - so if you're fighting it does less for you than if you're sitting. Why bother running the health chant mid-combat anyway? Its not like the pally health-chant.<br>
<br>
What I'd like to see is another offensive combat buff. I would like to see possibly a watered-down version of the Savage's dps increase buff. That thing kicks ass, and if skalds had a little bit of that, it would be awesome. Two skalds in a group, one is adding raw damage to the end of each swing, the other skald is increasing the effectiveness of each weapon. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kilbane>Kilbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#ff0000>(11/26/03 11:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=734.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Improving Skalds</span><hr size=1> Voted for Group enhancement. Most times in RvR, Skalds are just speed bots. Two skalds in a group, usually one runs speed the other DA chant, three skalds in a group, one runs, speed, the second run DA chant and the third runs regen.<br>
<br>
Having 3 skalds in a group usually means two are running useful chants while the third runs something that not as effective except for down time relief.<br>
<br>
Would like to see alittle something extra added that would make our BS line alittle more useful in a group.<br>
